5_22.description: Chicago Bulls guard Tomáš Satoransky explodes in transition for the big-time slam against the Charlotte Hornets on November 23, 2019.

5_95.description: Not today! Phoenix Suns forward Kelly Oubre Jr. swats a corner three with authority against the Orlando Magic on January 10, 2020.

5_1.description: Make 'em dance, Trae! Atlanta Hawks breakout star Trae Young shakes San Antonio Spurs vet Lamarcus Aldridge before dishing the rock for a sweet two-handed dunk on November 5, 2019.

5_71.description: Anthony Davis of the Los Angeles Lakers gets up (way up!) for the massive two-handed alley-oop slam against the Phoenix Suns on January 1, 2020.

5_28.description: Chicago Bulls big man Luke Kornet gets out on the break and and glides to the rim for a sweet one-handed dunk in transition against the Cleveland Cavaliers on January 25, 2020.

5_43.description: Milwaukee Bucks youngster Donte DiVincenzo shows off his sick hops with a massive one-handed slam against the Cleveland Cavaliers on December 14, 2019.

5_149.description: Portland Trail Blazers center Hassan Whiteside sends Damion Lee of the Golden State Warriors packing with a nasty block on January 20, 2020.
